This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses various techniques such as knowledge distillation, policy gradient fine-tuning, and the use of input token fertilities as a latent variable, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV, in that order.
